comments: Duren (DET) brings his hands toward Branham (SAS) and marginal contact occurs as Duren (DET) releases away to roll.
Collins (SAS) jumps alongside Duren's (DET) path  and absorbs the marginal body contact during Duren's upward shooting motion.
Collins (SAS) establishes himself in Ivey's (DET) path and gives him a step to avoid the contact.
Bogdanovic (DET) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Duren (DET) places his forearm to Collins' (SAS) side and marginal body contact occurs during Collins' shot attempt at the basket.
Bogdanovic (DET) places his hand to Collins' (SAS) side as he sets the screen and immediately slides his hand off as they disengage.
Branham (SAS) is moving alongside Ivey's (DET) path and marginal body contact occurs during Ivey's (DET) drive.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Bates-Diop's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Bates-Diop's (SAS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Graham (SAS) places his bent forearm to Livers' (DET) side and absorbs the marginal contact defending his drive to the basket.
Collins (SAS) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Duren (DET) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Ivey (DET) briefly grasps Johnson's (SAS) arm and immediately disengages as he slips the contact.
Collins (SAS) and Livers (DET) engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Duren (DET) places his hand to Collins' (SAS) arm as they come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Johnson (SAS) makes contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Ivey (DET) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Ivey (DET) legally regains possession of the ball in the backcourt after it is deflected by Johnson (SAS).

Duren (DET) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Johnson (SAS) contests Bogdanovic's (DET) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.

Johnson (SAS) initiates contact with Ivey's (DET) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Branham (SAS) establishes himself in Duren's (DET) path and absorbs the contact.

Hayes (DET) defends Graham (SAS) off-ball and briefly places his hands against his sides before correcting.

24 second violation is correctly whistled against SAS.
